gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Warriors 127, 76ers 104
gameRecap.excerpt: The Warriors defeated the 76ers, 127-104. Andrew Wiggins led Golden State with 21 points and 10 rebounds as Jonathan Kuminga (18 points, six rebounds, five assists) and Klay Thompson (18 points) totaled 36 points. KJ Martin led Philadelphia with 15 points as Patrick Beverley added 13 points and five assists. The Warriors have now won four of their last five games to improve to 23-25 while the 76ers are now 1-7 in their last eight games to move to 30-20.
